       title="Getting Started"
       id="Getting-Started">

    <primary-label ref="onboard"/>

    <p>
        This guide explains how to add Kore to your project and verify that the setup works correctly.
    </p>

    <p>
        Kore is published on Maven Central and can be used in both JVM-only and Kotlin Multiplatform projects.
        The setup is intentionally lightweight so it can be added to new and existing Gradle builds with minimal effort.
    </p>

    <chapter title="Requirements" id="requirements">
        <p>Before adding Kore, make sure your project meets the following requirements:</p>
        <list>
            <li>Gradle with Kotlin DSL.</li>
            <li>A configured <code>mavenCentral()</code> repository.</li>
            <li>A Kotlin project set up for either JVM or Kotlin Multiplatform.</li>
        </list>
    </chapter>

