        <p><b>Key capabilities:</b></p>
        <list>
            <li>Works across <b>all major Kotlin targets</b> from a single <code>commonMain</code> dependency.</li>
            <li>Full <b>host testing support</b> including Android resources.</li>
            <li>Consistent APIs across platforms; platform-specific features where needed.</li>
        </list>
    </chapter>

    <chapter title="Installation" id="installation">
        <p>Choose the setup that matches your project type.</p>

        <tabs>
            <tab id="kmp-install" title="Kotlin Multiplatform">
                <p>
                    Add Kore to the <code>commonMain</code> source set so it is available from shared code.
                </p>
                <code-block lang="kotlin">
                    <![CDATA[kotlin {
                        sourceSets {
                            commonMain.dependencies {
                                implementation("com.davils:davilsx-kore:<latest>")
                            }
                        }
                    }]]>
                </code-block>
                <p><b>Details</b></p>
                <list>
                    <li>Use <code>commonMain</code> when Kore should be accessible from shared multiplatform code.</li>
                    <li>Platform source sets such as <code>jvmMain</code>, <code>androidMain</code>, or <code>iosMain</code> can use the shared integration.</li>
                    <li>Replace <code>&lt;latest&gt;</code> with the currently released version.</li>
                </list>
            </tab>

            <tab id="jvm-install" title="JVM">
                <p>
                    For JVM-only projects, add Kore directly to the main dependency block.
                </p>
                <code-block lang="kotlin">
                    <![CDATA[dependencies {
                        implementation("com.davils:davilsx-kore:<latest>")
                    }]]>
                </code-block>
                <p><b>Details</b></p>
                <list>
                    <li>This setup is suitable for backend services, CLI applications, desktop apps, and JVM libraries.</li>
                    <li>No additional multiplatform source set configuration is required.</li>
                    <li>Replace <code>&lt;latest&gt;</code> with the currently released version.</li>
                </list>
            </tab>
        </tabs>
    </chapter>

    <chapter title="Repository Configuration" id="repository-configuration">
        <p>Ensure that Maven Central is included in your repositories configuration.</p>
        <code-block lang="kotlin">
            <![CDATA[repositories {
                mavenCentral()
            }]]>
        </code-block>
        <p>
            If this repository is missing, Gradle will not be able to resolve the Kore artifact.
        </p>
    </chapter>

    <chapter title="Verify Installation" id="verify-installation">
        <p>
            After adding the dependency, refresh the Gradle project in your IDE and confirm that imports resolve correctly.
        </p>
        <code-block lang="kotlin"><![CDATA[import com.davils.kore.uuid.Uuid

fun main() {
    println(Uuid.randomUuidV4())
}]]></code-block>
        <p>
            If the code compiles and the import is recognized without errors, Kore has been added successfully.
        </p>
    </chapter>
</topic>